subtitle: You need foods in many colors
description: You need foods in many colors
title: Should I eat differently?
content:
Created by BabyCenter 



Now that you are pregnant, it is important to try to eat well so your baby will grow well. You and your growing baby need lots of different foods. 

A simple way to think about it is to eat lots of different colored foods! 

You could talk to your family about the food you need.

Try to eat some of each of these food types every day:

•	Fruit and vegetables. These help your baby be healthy.

•	Starchy foods. These include bread, rice, pasta, pumpkin and potatoes. These foods give you energy.

•	Foods rich in protein. These include eggs, dark green leafy vegetables, nuts, chicken, fish and meat. These help your baby grow well.

•	Calcium-rich and dairy foods. These include corn tortillas, milk, soy milk and broccoli. They help your baby grow strong bones.

[Eating well during pregnancy][1]


  [1]: http://www.babycenter.com/pregnancy-eating-well
